  "texts": [
    "We found that using the LLMs in both deductive and inductive research tasks, augmented the interpretive research process, making it possible to save time, observe things we had missed, and be more confident in our findings.",
    "We determined that the research process can incorporate LLMs when it comes to qualitative coding, including index coding, classification, and thematic analysis, and in responding to the researchers' analytical queries.",
    "There are several benefits associated with using LLMs in qualitative research.",
    "First, when it came to qualitative coding and classification tasks, the accessibility and power of the model streamlined and accelerated the research process, making it possible to accomplish more, more quickly.",
    "Second, compared with fully human analysis, the iterative nature of the human-machine interaction required transparency regarding background assumptions and ideas and clarity in the construction of concepts and qualitative codes."
